 of the effective number of carriers and that of the\nscattering time. The $T$-dependence of the resistivity displays a knee-like\nfeature which signals a cross-over to the intermediate-temperature regime where\nthe diffusion constant (or scattering time) start increasing with decreasing\n$T$. At high-temperatures, the thermopower obeys the Heikes formula, while the\nWiedemann-Franz law is violated with the Lorenz number vanishing as $1/T^2$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Aug 2016 16:22:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 10 Nov 2016 15:09:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-21"}
