ulting observed velocity function is\ncompared to velocity functions derived from cosmological simulations of the z =\n0 galaxy population. We find that dark matter-only simulations show a strong\nmismatch with the observed VF. Hydrodynamic simulations fare better, but still\ndo not fully reproduce observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Aug 2016 20:00:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-31"}
